node.text:
So pumped to be involved in this @fisthandwear / @livinorg / @JayWilson_6 project. It’s so important to speak up about your mental health and I encourage anyone that is going through bad times to speak up. Talk to your mates and your family about what your going through! And always be willing to ask your mates how they are because it could just save a life! 

This video turned out amazing and I hope it gives you guys a good look into how elite athletes deal with certain situations and circumstances! People often forget we are human too and although we live a great life it doesn’t mean it’s perfect. The amount of ups and downs we face doing what we do is crazy.

Head over to @mxstore MXstore.com.au and purchase some LIVIN gloves! All profits raised from this glove will go towards LIVINWell mental health educational program! Which aims to break the stigma around mental health!

node.text:
Once upon a time i took a trip to Melbourne to film a video with @kurtteague and this was the outcome! 
Back then, I had so many things I wanted to achieve within BMX and it’s crazy to me now that I achieved them and so much more. I always say it, but I’m FOREVER grateful for BMX
If you have a goal, stay dedicated and enjoy what you do🙌🏼

node.text:
HAPPY FATHERS DAY TO MY DAD AND TO ALL THE DADS OUT THERE 🙌🏼
I am very honoured to win @sportsdadoftheyear !  Thank you so much to everyone that voted for me, it means so much🙏🏼 
My dad has been dealing with emphysema for the past few years so I’m donating $5,000 to @lungfoundation to help with their research behind lung disease ❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Logan Martin in Gold Coast, Queensland. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
It almost feels unreal to hold up both these gold medals!!
2021 UCI World championship gold backed up by an OLYMPIC gold 🤯
My latest YouTube video reflects back on my last few months and then finishes up by riding the replica Tokyo Course we had built prior to the Olympics! Make sure you go check it out🙌🏼
Link in my bio!!
